# Experience Continuity Layer

A virtual OS with channel simulations (web, IVR, WhatsApp, kiosk, email).
An AI agent orchestrates all channels so a customer can switch without repeating themselves.

## Stack (decided)

Next.js 16 (App Router) · React 19 · TypeScript 5 · Zustand + Immer · Zod · Tailwind 4 · Lucide · Motion

## File structure

```
src/
  app/
    api/agent/respond/route.ts         # POST — agent reply
    api/agent/extract-context/route.ts  # POST — post-turn context extraction
    page.tsx                            # renders <VirtualOS />
    globals.css                         # design tokens + component CSS
  core/
    agent-context/
      types.ts          # TypeScript interfaces (source of truth)
      schema.ts         # Zod schemas for validation
      store.ts          # Zustand store + exported helpers
      prompt-builder.ts # builds system prompt from AgentContext
    ai/
      types.ts              # AgentAIRequest interface
      client.ts             # direct HTTP calls per provider
      agent-module.ts       # runAgentTurn orchestration
      context-extraction.ts # extraction prompt + parser
  components/shell/
    virtual-os.tsx                     # app definitions + OS layout
    taskbar/taskbar.tsx
    wallpaper-switcher.tsx
    window-manager/types.ts            # ShellAppId, AppDefinition, WindowState
    window-manager/use-window-manager.ts
    tooling/design-system/primitives.tsx  # all reusable UI primitives
    windows/                             # one file per window/channel
```

## Core architecture — non-negotiable

- `AgentContext` is the single shared memory. Every channel reads/writes it.
- AI calls are real (OpenAI, Anthropic, Google, HuggingFace). Provider, model, and key are runtime-configurable via `agentConfig`.
- System prompt is always built from `AgentContext` via `buildSystemPrompt()`.
- Channel handoffs are written to `AgentContext.channelHistory`.
- Channel IDs: `web`, `ivr`, `whatsapp`, `kiosk`, `email`.
- App IDs: `web-browser`, `ivr-phone`, `whatsapp`, `kiosk`, `email-client`, plus tool windows.
- Post-turn context extraction is fire-and-forget — never block the main flow.
- Errors from providers must be surfaced, never masked with simulated responses.

## How to work

- State architectural decisions explicitly before implementing.
- One phase at a time. Stop and wait before moving on.
- If reading an existing file with @, say so before modifying it.
- Run `typecheck` after significant changes.
- Periodically (for example after 5+ significant iterations), consider running the `optimize-engine` skill to review transcript history and propose rule/skill updates.
